<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUN 92 / Tighter scrutiny by BR fund
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH RAIL Pension Trustee Company, which manages Pounds 8bn in
pension-fund assets, has pledged to monitor more closely the management of
companies in which it has a significant stake.
The move is a sign of the growing restiveness among institutional investors,
who are demanding more information about companies they invest in and the
ability to effect management changes.
The BR fund - one of the largest in the public sector - is the first scheme
to announce a policy on corporate governance since the publication last
month of the Cadbury report urging wide-ranging reforms.
The BR scheme said: 'BRPTC's corporate governance policy has two main aims:
to support and promote efficient and effective equity markets and to protect
shareholder value.'
The policy calls on the scheme to vote on all resolutions placed before
company meetings.
</TEXT>
