<TEXT>
CORNING, the US specialty glass group, yesterday turned in underlying
second-quarter earnings of Dollars 88.4m, or 47 cents a share, a 15 per cent
advance on the same period last year.
However, net income was reduced by a pre-tax charge of Dollars 16.3m linked
to a special charge to cover costs related to silicone breast implants at
