<TEXT>
GENERAL Electric of the US and Hitachi of Japan have announced an expansion
of their long-standing co-operative agreements, opening up new opportunities
for GE to export power transmission and distribution technology to Japan.
The two companies said yesterday they had entered into long-term
co-operative agreements designed to strengthen their competitive position in
the utility transmission and distribution market.
The agreements extend for another 10 years the companies' joint venture,
launched in 1977, to market high-voltage breakers in the US. The venture
