technology.
Obtaining access to the Japanese transmission and distribution market is a
significant boost for GE, complementing the position it has already
established in power generating equipment. GE is prime contractor on Tokyo
Electric Power's 2,800MW combined cycle plant, the largest in the world,
which is due for completion in the mid-1990s.
