OMV, the Austrian oil company, is facing a sharp drop in 1992 earnings
following a loss in the first five months of the year.
The company, which is majority-controlled by the state holding group
Austrian Industries (AI), is said to have suffered a Sch100m (Dollars 9m)
shortfall in the January-May period, mostly because of losses at its
plastics subsidiary PCD.
The fiscal year's poor start could cut the full-year operating profit to
