undertake its scheduled initial public stock flotation in 1993, industry
sources say.
OMV generates nearly half of its parent company's annual earnings. An OMV
spokesman declined to confirm the figures, which were reported in the
Austrian press.
For the first quarter, OMV reported a loss of Sch300m, but the company's
results usually improve in the course of the year. Industry sources say OMV
still aims for an operating profit of Sch1.5bn for 1992, which would permit
the company to keep its dividend at Sch20 a share.
